    "answer_id" : 21209803,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<h1>IntelliJ 15, 2016 &amp; 2017</h1>\n\n<p>Similar to that discussed below for IntelliJ 13 &amp; 14, but with an extra level in the Settings/Preferences panel: <em>Settings</em> > <em>Build, Execution, Deployment</em> > <em>Compiler</em> > <em>Java Compiler</em>.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mlaEJ.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/mlaEJ.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<h1>IntelliJ 13 &amp; 14</h1>\n\n<p>In IntelliJ 13 and 14, check the <em>Settings > Compiler > Java Compiler</em> UI to ensure you're not targeting a different bytecode version in your module.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/5iI0X.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5474570,
      "reputation" : 21,
      "user_id" : 4352875,
      "user_type" : "unregistered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/bf68dd35f1fae4eb27dea915f3b37d6b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "mati",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4352875/mati"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1418365799,
