    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 62,
    "last_activity_date" : 1430752766,
    "last_edit_date" : 1430752766,
    "creation_date" : 1428444721,
    "answer_id" : 29502281,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In <strong>IntelliJ IDEA 14.1</strong> the \"Target bytecode version\" is in a different place.</p>\n\n<p>The following change worked for me:</p>\n\n<p><strong>File > Settings... > Build, Execution, Deployment > Compiler > Java Compiler</strong> : change <strong>Target bytecode version</strong> from 1.5 to 1.8</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/W4NaV.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/3qibL.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1430076,
        "reputation" : 763,
        "user_id" : 1352672,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ed7eaf74ba3b5b5429721973850216bd?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Shehaaz",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1352672/shehaaz"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1434825107,
      "post_id" : 30711520,
      "comment_id" : 49947725,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Thanks this worked for me! Don&#39;t forget to do &quot;Make Module &#39;[your app name]&#39;&quot; by right clicking on the project"
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2400125,
      "reputation" : 9704,
      "user_id" : 2097974,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 50,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/rQpMC.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Joe Cheng",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2097974/joe-cheng"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1433772857,
    "creation_date" : 1433772857,
    "answer_id" : 30711520,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Modify the compiler setting file of the project in the following path and change the 'target' to 1.7:</p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>/project/.idea/compiler.xml</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;bytecodeTargetLevel&gt;\n  &lt;module name=\"project-name\" target=\"1.7\" /&gt;\n&lt;/bytecodeTargetLevel&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 124298,
      "reputation" : 4124,
      "user_id" : 319302,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/19774763833bc515bdb35787c4234fa7?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Cagatay Kalan",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/319302/cagatay-kalan"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1460423693,
    "creation_date" : 1460423693,
    "answer_id" : 36561964,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If it is a Gradle project, in your build.gradle file, search for following settings:</p>\n\n<pre><code>sourceCompatibility = \"xx\"\ntargetCompatibility = \"xx\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>For all subrpojects, in your root build.gradle file, you may put:</p>\n\n<pre><code>subprojects { project -&gt;\n    sourceCompatibility = \"1.7\"\n    targetCompatibility = \"1.7\"\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Although you can manually set language levels in Idea > Settings, if it is a Gradle project, Idea automatically synchronizes module .iml files from Gradle settings ( tested with Idea 15+). So all your manual changes are overriden when gradle is refreshed. </p>\n\n<p>Based on <a href=\"https://docs.gradle.org/current/userguide/java_plugin.html\" rel=\"nofollow\">Gradle documentation</a>, if these are not set, then current JVM configuration is used. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1201625,
      "reputation" : 6905,
      "user_id" : 1172174,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 80,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/5vijs.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Gus",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1172174/gus"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1466791142,
    "creation_date" : 1466791142,
    "answer_id" : 38019478,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I found another way to run into this error. You can get this if you have been re-organizing your directory structure, and one of your poms is pointing to the old parent which no-longer configures javac (because that configuration was moved to a middle level). If this happens the top level defaults to 1.5 and the misbehaving lower level pom inherits it.</p>\n\n<p>So another thing to check when you see this error is that your pom structure is matching your directory structure properly.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1689601,
      "reputation" : 129,
      "user_id" : 1552241,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96f7e64ee4056c5527b21574f46e9c31?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Viraj Kulkarni",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1552241/viraj-kulkarni"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1478731195,
    "creation_date" : 1478731195,
    "answer_id" : 40517191,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Make sure right depency is selected.\nFile > Project Structure</p>\n\n<p>Select your project and navigate to Dependencies tab. Select right dependancy from dropdown or create new. </p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1532531,
      "reputation" : 38631,
      "user_id" : 1429387,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 63,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/LVOVA.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "naXa stands with Ukraine",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1429387/naxa-stands-with-ukraine"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1501147257,
    "creation_date" : 1501147257,
    "answer_id" : 45346494,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If Maven build works fine, try to synchronizing structure of Maven and IntelliJ IDEA projects.</p>\n\n<p>In the <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/help/idea/maven-projects-tool-window.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Maven tool window</a>, click refresh button <a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KupZQ.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/KupZQ.png\" alt=\"refresh\"></a>. On pressing this button, IntelliJ IDEA parses the project structure in the Maven tool window.</p>\n\n<p>Note that this might not help if you're using EAP build, since Maven synchronization feature may be broken sometimes.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 52873,
        "reputation" : 2583,
        "user_id" : 158037,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b1b81dd76dea2a6e58fa4c8606301e92?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "user158037",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/158037/user158037"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1642676605,
      "post_id" : 49980817,
      "comment_id" : 125136915,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "I had a case when this didn&#39;t help either. But since I knew that build worked fine in CLI, I knew the issue had to be somewhere in the IDEA. JDK version/level was set to 17 <i>everywhere</i>. Finally simply using &quot;File / Invalidate Caches ...&quot; solved the problem. I just don&#39;t know if deleting project&#39;s &quot;.idea/&quot; was also required."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "user_type" : "does_not_exist",
      "display_name" : "user7375303"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1524485600,
    "creation_date" : 1524485600,
    "answer_id" : 49980817,
    "question_id" : 12900373,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If all the previous solutions haven't worked for you (which was my case), you can delete intellij config files:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/compiler.xml</li>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/encodings.xml</li>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/misc.xml</li>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/modules.xml</li>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/vcs.xml</li>\n<li>project_directory/.idea/workspace.xml</li>\n<li>etc.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Intellij will regenerate new ones later.\n<strong>However, BE CAREFUL, this will also delete all intellij configuration made  on the projet (i.e: configuration of debug mode, ...)</strong></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6987823,
      "reputation" : 4377,
      "user_id" : 5358054,
      "user_type" : "registered",
